The "transport/overhead" here is essentially how long it takes for the witness data to move from the EL to the CL via the EngineAPI.

This was the way it was calculated;
`Total_Round_Trip_Latency (CL Side) - (Block_Execution + Witness_Generation + JSON_Serialization (EL Side))`

Why is that?

When I saw to log, it felt reasonable to me, the log I mean.


```
if witness && proofs != nil {
        serStart := time.Now()
        encoded, err := rlp.EncodeToBytes(proofs)
        serDuration := time.Since(serStart)
        if err != nil {
            log.Warn("Failed to serialize witness", "err", err)
        } else {
            log.Info("[WITNESS_BENCH] Approx Serialization Time", "block", block.Number(), "duration", serDuration)
            log.Info("[WITNESS_BENCH] Witness Size", "block", block.Number(), "bytes", len(encoded))
            wb := hexutil.Bytes(encoded)
            witnessBytes = &wb
        }
    }
```


